The yearly Bunty release.

Part of a group of four sister titles for girls published by D.C. Thomson & Co.. The names of the four titles are Bunty, Judy, Mandy and Debbie. Each title had an accompanying weekly, monthly, and annual volume:

Bunty

  • Weekly: Bunty
  • Monthly: Bunty Picture Story Library for Girls
  • Annual: Bunty Annual

Debbie

  • Weekly: Debbie
  • Monthly: Debbie Picture Story Library For Girls
  • Annual: Debbie For Girls Annual

Judy

  • Weekly: Judy
  • Monthly: Judy Picture Story Library For Girls
  • Annual: Judy For Girls Annual

Mandy

  • Weekly: Mandy
  • Monthly: Mandy Picture Story Library For Girls
  • Annual: Mandy For Girls Annual
name: Bunty For Girls Annual

description:
Two-Fisted Historical Adventure.

Rupert's Land, 1755. Follow famed adventurer, Charles Lord as he and a small band of survivors flee into the wilderness after a band of French mercenaries ambush England's Fort Newcastle. Charles's only hope for survival is to unite the various people of the land and of his past against this new threat. Set in the vast wooded expanses of Canada, Northwest Passage marks the beginning of an ongoing two-fisted historical-action series.

Also available is Annotated Northwest Passage
name: Northwest Passage
